PenguinMic Audio Recorder

---

Welcome to PenguinMic!

PenguinMic lets you record, play, and share audio directly in PenguinMod.

---

Usage

1️⃣ Record

Block: start recording

Starts recording audio from your microphone.

Audio is represented in memory as raw floats.

Does nothing if already recording.

2️⃣ Stop recording

Block: stop recording

Stop recording audio.

Please make sure to stop before playing or downloading your recording.

3️⃣ Play recording

Block: play recording

Plays back everything you recorded.

Must stop recording first, prior to playback.

4️⃣ Play samples

Block: play samples [SAMPLES]

Plays an array of raw audio samples.

SAMPLES can be

JSON array: [0.1, -0.2, 0.5]

CSV string: 0.1, -0.2, 0.5

Scratch list converted to string

Samples should be in the range -1 to 1.

5️⃣ Mic sample reporter

Block: mic sample

Returns the newest single audio sample (float) from the mic in real time.

6️⃣ Get recorded data

Block: Recorded data (json)

Returns your recording as a JSON array of floats.

Can be used with play samples() or shared between projects.

7️⃣ Recording length

Block: recording length (samples)

Returns the number of audio samples in your current recording.

8️⃣ Recording clear

Block: clear recording

Clears the internal recording buffer and frees memory.

9️⃣ Set max recording seconds

Block: set max recording seconds to [SECONDS]

Limits how long recordings can be, prevents huge memory usage.

Default is 30 seconds.

Download WAV

Block: download recording (wav) [FILENAME]

Exports your recording as a 16‑bit PCM WAV file.

Example: download recording (wav) "myvoice.wav"

Tips

Stop recording before calling play recording for smooth playback. If you only need a short clip, consider setting max seconds to a lower value to save memory. Use get recorded data + play samples to share audio between projects.
